{
  "narration": "The two of you pause as you reach the outskirts of the Forgotten Waystation. The ruins loom before you, moss-covered stone walls half-collapsed and choked with tangled underbrush. Frost lingers in the shaded hollows, and only a faint shaft of sunlight pierces the overgrown archway--once a proud marker of safe passage for travelers, now a silent witness to the frontier's troubles.\n\nKira crouches low, scanning the trampled grass and churned mud. \"This is definitely where the trail leads,\" she murmurs, eyes sharp. She points to a series of irregular drag marks winding through the weeds, leading toward the shadowed entryway. \"See here? Someone dragged something heavy. The prints match the ones by the crates at Trader's Rest. I'd bet my bow the saboteur doubled back here after the sabotage.\"\n\nShe glances at the low, collapsed wall where a few battered crates are half-buried in the dirt. \"You're right, Eirik--something was dragged down here. These ruins would make a perfect spot to stash contraband or set up an ambush.\"\n\nThe air is tense, silent but for the occasional caw of a distant crow. No monsters or traps are obvious, but shadows linger beneath the stone arches and broken roof, promising secrets yet to be revealed. Kira whispers, \"Do you want to scout the ruins for threats, search for hidden evidence, or follow the drag marks deeper? If you want to look for danger, a Perception check might help. If you're searching for clues, Investigation is your friend.\"\n\nWhat do you do, Eirik?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 4
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira gives you a small, confident smile, her hand already moving to her bow. \"You watch my back, I'll see what secrets they've left behind.\"\n\nAs you scan the overgrown ruins for any lurking threats, Kira slinks off toward the drag marks, her elven senses keen for any sign of hidden caches or coded messages.\n\nEirik, please make a Perception check. Roll a d20 and add your Perception modifier.\n\nMeanwhile, Kira will attempt an Investigation check to uncover clues hidden among the ruins. She narrows her eyes, crouching low by the mossy debris and begins her search.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 4
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You scan the Forgotten Waystation with a veteran's eye, your senses sharpened by hard-earned instinct. The ruins are hushed but not silent: a faint rustle betrays the retreat of a field mouse, and distant crows caw as if mocking the human folly that once flourished here. You catch the subtle glint of sunlight on cold metal--an old, half-buried signal mirror, nothing dangerous, but its presence reminds you how the rangers once relied on vigilance and cleverness.\n\nNo threats reveal themselves--no lurking bandits, no shadowy figures at the edge of your vision. The place feels recently abandoned, but safe for the moment. Your watchfulness is rewarded with peace of mind, and you can focus on the task at hand.\n\nMeanwhile, Kira kneels by the drag marks and overgrown crates. She rummages carefully, following the signs with practiced fingers. \"There,\" she calls softly, extracting a battered lockbox from beneath a tangle of ferns. Inside, you both discover sabotage tools--snipped wires, vials of oily black residue, and a coded letter marked with a silver-stitch crow's feather insignia. Kira flips through a sheaf of maps showing caravan routes and bell post locations. \"They were planning more than just a single hit. Scout's Watch is marked as the next target. And look at this--timing, patrol schedules, everything. The Crow's Hand is organized.\"\n\nShe hands you the coded letter, her brow furrowed. \"Any chance you can make sense of this, Eirik? Or should we bring it to Elen first? Either way, this is proof enough to warn the Rangers and the traders. What now?\"",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
