      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You take a steadying breath, the coded letter crackling in your hands as you study the jagged script and arcane symbols. The unfamiliar cipher twists across the page, but you recognize patterns from your days sending urgent missives during the border wars. If only you can tease out the meaning, there might be precious time to warn Scout's Watch before the next assault.\n\nKira keeps watch, her bow casually ready, eyes darting between the overgrown arches. \"Take your time, Eirik. If there's anyone who can crack a code written by desperate men, it's a soldier who learned to pray with one hand and write in code with the other.\"\n\nPlease make an Intelligence (Investigation) check to attempt to decode the letter. Roll a d20 and add your Investigation modifier.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You frown in concentration, carefully turning the coded letter in your hands, searching for familiar patterns and keys from your days in the field. The symbols and obscure phrases blur together, frustratingly resistant to your best efforts. Try as you might, the meaning remains just out of reach--the Crow's Hand were clever, and their cipher is nothing like the simple military codes you once used.\n\nKira glances over, offering a sympathetic shrug. \"Don't beat yourself up, Eirik. Even a master tracker can't follow a trail that's been washed away. Maybe Elen or one of the senior rangers has seen something like this before. At least we've got enough to warn them, even if we can't break their code right now.\"\n\nThe ruins remain quiet, the evidence secured in your pack. With the immediate danger passed, you can decide whether to return to the Rangers' Command Post, check in with Trader Sila, or take a moment to rest and gather your thoughts. What will you do next?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira considers your question, her gaze drifting back down the overgrown trail toward Trader's Rest. She taps her chin thoughtfully. \"We hit the big ones along the main route: the relay at the Rangers' Command Post, Trader's Rest, and this old waystation.\" She glances at the battered maps retrieved from the cache, running a finger along the marked network lines.\n\n\"There are posts deeper in the Thornwood, but those mostly connect to the northern patrol trails--not the main supply road. If the saboteurs were going to make another move, I'd guess Scout's Watch is next. It's marked all over these notes, and it's the crossroads for rangers coming out of the wilds.\"\n\nShe rolls up the map and shoulders her pack, her voice softening. \"If you want to be thorough, we could double back and check the lines between here and Scout's Watch. But with what we found, Elen will want to see the evidence. Your call, Eirik. Do we press north, circle back to Sila, or report in at the outpost first?\"\n\nKira looks to you expectantly, trusting your judgment. What do you want to do next?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "With grim determination, you and Kira gather up the evidence and prepare to make for Scout's Watch. The urgency presses at your heels as you leave the overgrown ruins, retracing your path through the wilds. Kira moves swiftly ahead, bow ready, scanning for any sign of threat along the route. The trail is quiet save for the distant caw of crows and the whisper of wind through tangled branches.\n\nAfter a cautious journey, the landscape opens to reveal Scout's Watch: a modest riverside post flanked by mist-shrouded waters and ancient tree roots, its silver bell glinting faintly atop a sturdy wooden tower. A handful of rangers move about the clearing, warily watching the approach from the direction of the ruins. At your arrival, one of the rangers steps forward, hand resting on the hilt of his sword, brow furrowed in concern.\n\nKira raises a reassuring hand. \"We bring news! The Crow's Hand is targeting this place next. Saboteurs have mapped your routines.\" The rangers tense, exchanging worried glances as you reveal the coded letter and tactical maps, the weight of your warning settling over Scout's Watch like a gathering storm.\n\nWhat do you want to do next, Eirik? Warn the commander, search for sabotage, or help set extra defenses while you investigate?",
  "actions": [
