}

{
  "narration": "You and Kira cross the open ground of Scout's Watch, your boots crunching softly on the damp earth as the swirling river mist parts before you. Rangers move about with wary efficiency, their eyes lingering on the silver bell tower and the woods beyond. The tension is palpable--word of sabotage and bandit attacks has clearly reached even this remote post.\n\nAs you approach, Ranger Marcus--a grizzled veteran with a mouth set in a hard line--steps forward to intercept you. He recognizes Kira and nods, but his gaze quickly fixes on you, searching for answers. \"I heard you brought trouble nipping at your heels, Eirik. What's the word from the ruins?\"\n\nKira steps in, voice urgent but steady. \"We recovered proof. The Crow's Hand plans to strike here next. They've mapped your patrols, bell posts, and caravan schedules. We have coded messages, tactical maps, and a cache of sabotage tools.\"\n\nMarcus's frown deepens as he takes the evidence from you, glancing through the documents and coded note with practiced eyes. \"We'd best get these to Elen and the other rangers. If they've marked us for attack, every hand here will have to be ready.\"\n\nHe gestures for you to follow. \"Let's bring this to Ranger Elen. She should hear it from you herself.\" As you make your way toward the central campfire where Elen confers with several scouts, Marcus leans in, voice low. \"Anything else you learned--anything strange or out of place? The Crow's Hand doesn't usually work alone.\"\n\nDo you want to share what you know about the coded messages, the strange lights or supernatural hints, or ask Elen for help deciphering the letter? Or do you have other concerns for the rangers before preparing a defense?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}
